== Remixing Social Production
1. The GNU GPL: Consumers own and control the sources of production.
2. Time Banks: Workers gain sources when they commit to work in the future.
3. The Land Value Tax (LVT): Users gain sources when they pay profit.
4. Cell Structure: Subgroups split sources when realistically divisible.


== Projects
Earth Change: A new way for groups to own and control the production they need.
For Product: Using property ownership to minimize rent, interest and profit.
Source Title: CryptoCoin backed by permacultured land and low-tech solutions.

